OL,3,CThe Devon charity tackling addiction
OL,4,Cthrough exercise
OL,6,FAfter two years operating as a
OL,7,Fcommunity group, Addicts to Athletes
OL,8,Fbecame a registered charity in August.
OL,10,FA number of their activity leaders
OL,11,Fhave lived experience of addiction
OL,12,Fthemselves.
OL,14,F"Being in addiction is quite a lonely
OL,15,Fplace, you do lose your social skills
OL,16,Fover a period of time," said volunteer
OL,17,FMike. "Just getting out and talking,
OL,18,Feven just once a week, can be very
OL,19,Fbeneficial."
OL,1,W~s1{$~k4{$k7                    G3/9
